     Returns {@code x mod m}, a non-negative value less than {@code m}. This differs from {@code x %
m}, which might be negative.

<p>For example:

{@snippet :
mod(7, 4) == 3
mod(-7, 4) == 1
mod(-1, 4) == 3
mod(-8, 4) == 0
mod(8, 4) == 0
}

